	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It's pretty simple. The game tells the FDS bios, I want X file from X disk. So the system checks the disk and each side has a header telling which side of the disk it is, A or B. If that fails it tells you to switch sides. When the correct disk is inserted it loads the requested file. That's all there is to it. Read the FDS doc by Brad Taylor I believe it is. If you can't do it after that, forget about it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
